<title>JAPAN: Japan vehicle exports and sales seen up in 1997/98.</title>
<headline>Japan vehicle exports and sales seen up in 1997/98.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>All eleven Japanese automobile manufacturers' forecasts of domestic sales, exports and overseas production for the year to March 1998 were disclosed by Thursday, as follows (with percentage changes from a year earlier):</p>
<p>				  DOMESTIC SALES  YR/YR PCT</p>
<p> Toyota		2,240,000     +0.4</p>
<p> Nissan Motor	1,140,000     +1.2</p>
<p> Honda Motor	   800,000     +2.2</p>
<p> Mitsubishi Motors   860,000    +11.4</p>
<p> Mazda		   415,000    +10.1</p>
<p> Suzuki Motor	  635,000     -1.7</p>
<p> Daihatsu Motor	495,000     +2.9</p>
<p> Fuji Heavy	    360,000     +3.9</p>
<p> Isuzu Motors	  153,000     -3.2</p>
<p> Nissan Diesel	  34,000     -2.6</p>
<p> Hino Motors	    47,000     -3.5</p>
<p> Total			    7,179,000     +2.5</p>
<p>---------------------------------------------</p>
<p>				    EXPORTS	 YR/YR</p>
<p> Toyota			   1,400,000     +6.7</p>
<p> Nissan Motor		     620,000     +3.6</p>
<p> Honda Motor			470,000    +15.1</p>
<p> Mitsubishi Motors		480,000     +0.2</p>
<p> Mazda				505,000     +8.4</p>
<p> Suzuki Motor		     222,000    +10.4</p>
<p> Daihatsu Motor		   102,000    +36.0</p>
<p> Fuji Heavy			 110,000    +32.0</p>
<p> Isuzu Motors		     208,000     +8.9</p>
<p> Nissan Diesel		     21,000     -6,2</p>
<p> Hino Motors			 34,000     +1.0</p>
<p> Total			    4,172,000     +7.8</p>
<p>---------------------------------------------</p>
<p>				OVERSEAS OUTPUT   YR/YR</p>
<p> Toyota			   1,520,000    +10.2</p>
<p> Nissan Motor		   1,101,000     +2.0</p>
<p> Honda Motor		    1,140,000     +7.9</p>
<p> Mitsubishi Motors		880,000    +15.3</p>
<p> Mazda				140,000     -5.4</p>
<p> Suzuki Motor		   1,034,000     +1.4</p>
<p> Daihatsu Motor		   242,000     -5.7</p>
<p> Fuji Heavy			 101,000     -6.0</p>
<p> Isuzu Motors		     361,000     -0.6</p>
<p> Total			    6,519,000    +10.2</p>
</text>
